metadata.name: Modulacions (audio) #31
metadata.description:
Modulacions (Modulations): modulation with an oscillator (carrier) with an LFO (modulator). 

-The LFO is controlled by  some of fxhash characters

-Some parameters are randomly assigned to each of the possible characters of the fxhash string (0,1,2....X,Y,Z): carrier frequency, maximum and minimum frequencies of the modulator, waveforms, views etc.

-A number of fxhash characters are selected (8,16,24,32, 40 or 48), and in order they are played and displayed using the assigned values.

-Each character is encoded in binary-> the LFO frequency is controlled: 1->maximum frequency, 0->minimum frequency.

Features:
Â·dark: black (true) or white (false).
Â·carrier_wave: wave shape of carrier oscillator (sine, square, triangle or sawtooth)
Â·modulator_mult: value of LFO multiplier.
Â·modulator_sum: value added to LFO amplitude.
Â·num_fxhash_chars: number of fxhash characters used (8,16,24,32, 40 or 48)
Â·bits_display: bits string visualization (3 types)
Â·carrier_freq_range: frequency range of carrier (low, mid or high).
Â·frames_per_bit: duration of each bit in frames.(15,20,25 or 30)

-NOTE: Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated.

-p5js and p5.sound

Shift is the result of an exploration into this space, basing its existence on two principles â€” dissection and vertical shifting. Each variable in this art engine has been meticulously weighted, giving rise to high diversity and the possibility of epic combinations.

metadata.name: Social Barriers #20
metadata.description:
When it comes to social barriers, they can often be thought of as bubbles. Just like bubbles, they can be easily affected by those around them and if they come into contact with one another, they can explode. In the context of culture, social barriers can limit the mixing of cultures. This is because individuals from different cultures can often be hesitant to interact with those from other cultures, for fear of offending them or not being able to relate to them. This can lead to the formation of cultural bubbles, where people only interact with those who are from the same culture. Social barriers have some negative effects because it can be difficult for cultures to mix and evolve or grow if there is a lack of understanding or respect for one another.
- Dark, Light and Gold modes
- hit 's' to save hi res .png

metadata.name: Tails of Majestic Creatures #120
metadata.description:
Excerpt from the Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

"Some of the fantastically colored reeds that grow in clumps along the banks of the Tezonian river have profoundly affected the local inhabitants' culture, and beliefs.

Legend tells of how there lived majestic creatures, that were so beautiful, and dazzling, that they greatly offended Nocturna - the Deity of the Night. After many unsuccessful attempts to get rid of them, usually foiled by the clever Majestic Creatures in elaborate ways, Nocturna cast a powerful spell upon them. This spell was extremely effective and made the Majestic Creatures plummet, with great speed, into the ground leaving only their tails to show.

The creatures then turned their energy to nature, and joined as one to become a deity of the natural world. They rise, and protect creatures from harm, especially during the night.

The reeds (tails) are held as sacred, and believed to have healing powers.

I have created this graphical study of the tails (exotic reeds) for your informational requirements and ocular interest.

128 images are planned to follow henceforth, subject to available minters."

s will save a 4000x4000 jpg of the image. 
g will convert to gray.
c will convert back to color.
m will save a 4000x4000 monochrome jpg of the image.

Coded in P5.js
